SaveName: DBR - Scots Common vs Early Tudor English - v1.5 - 2026-01-14 17:48:09
Note:
De Bellis Renationis - Scots Common vs Early Tudor English

Recent Updates (2026-01-14):
✅ All 24 area terrain with smooth 16-point organic polygon boundaries (not rectangles!)
✅ Coastal waterway resized to 4ft × 0.5-2ft variable width
✅ Hills rescaled for proper DBR visibility (0.15-0.28)
✅ Measuring stick colored red/black alternating
✅ Generic assets renamed (removed French prefix from baggage, ships, artillery)
✅ Wagon Laager added (defensive fortification)

Layout:
• Main table: 6×4 feet grass surface (GitHub hosted)
• Side tables: 2×3.5 feet for terrain bag (left) and units (right)
• 37 terrain pieces in green bag on main table
• 33 units neatly arranged on right side table (scale 0.039 for 40mm bases)
• 3 dice bags (red, green, purple - 30 dice total)

All assets hosted on GitHub: https://github.com/krumphau/DBR_assets
Commits: c7c41ea (organic terrain), 48c0ffd (coastal resize), 
         320db84 (asset renaming), 32caf1d (wagon laager)
